WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.203 --> 00:00:05.439
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

2
00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

3
00:00:44.579 --> 00:00:46.079
[masked man 1]
Let's go. Let's go.

4
00:00:46.213 --> 00:00:47.715
-[machine beeps]
-[sighs]

5
00:00:50.952 --> 00:00:52.185
[door rattles]

6
00:00:53.253 --> 00:00:56.089
Hey! The machine's broken.

7
00:00:56.223 --> 00:00:58.026
I want my $40.

8
00:00:58.726 --> 00:01:00.695
Come on.
I can see you in there.

9
00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:03.297
Come on.

10
00:01:05.700 --> 00:01:07.067
Hey.

11
00:01:09.169 --> 00:01:10.437
[gunshots]

12
00:01:12.774 --> 00:01:15.009
<i>Come on.</i>
<i>I can see you in there.</i>

13
00:01:15.142 --> 00:01:16.578
[gunshots]

14
00:01:16.711 --> 00:01:18.513
Oof! For 40 bucks.

15
00:01:19.581 --> 00:01:22.215
-[gagging]
-You okay. Mr. Price?

16
00:01:22.349 --> 00:01:23.851
Why did this happen
at my branch?

17
00:01:23.985 --> 00:01:25.587
This is so unfair.

18
00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:26.955
-I'm sure the dead guy
feels the same.
-[sirens wailing]

19
00:01:27.087 --> 00:01:28.488
[sighs]

20
00:01:28.990 --> 00:01:30.658
Here. take a seat.

21
00:01:30.792 --> 00:01:32.560
The camera on the ATM
is the only video feed
they didn't cut.

22
00:01:32.694 --> 00:01:34.662
Yeah. they took out
the phone lines
and the Wi-Fi too.

23
00:01:34.796 --> 00:01:36.664
That's why the gunshots
didn't trigger the alarm.

24
00:01:36.798 --> 00:01:40.902
-Okay. Mr. Price.
can you show us...
-[groaning]

25
00:01:41.703 --> 00:01:43.470
Okay. yeah.
You just keep doing that.

26
00:01:43.605 --> 00:01:45.540
-We're gonna take
a look around.
-[sighs]

27
00:01:45.673 --> 00:01:47.174
No footage
from inside the bank.

28
00:01:47.307 --> 00:01:48.308
No fingerprints yet.

29
00:01:48.442 --> 00:01:50.143
And our only witness is dead.

30
00:01:55.016 --> 00:01:56.249
Huh.

31
00:02:00.153 --> 00:02:01.455
Whoa. That's weird.

32
00:02:01.589 --> 00:02:03.390
-What's weird?
-The chemo.

33
00:02:03.524 --> 00:02:05.960
It made my vision
dull. kind of blurry.

34
00:02:06.094 --> 00:02:09.429
But now that that's over.
everything's a lot clearer.

35
00:02:09.564 --> 00:02:12.132
I can see better than I could
before the cancer.

36
00:02:14.035 --> 00:02:15.536
What if it's a superpower?

37
00:02:16.436 --> 00:02:18.271
What if it's normal eyesight?

38
00:02:19.007 --> 00:02:21.843
Okay. Bring your mere
mortal eyeballs over here.

39
00:02:22.510 --> 00:02:24.045
Take a look at these boxes.

40
00:02:24.779 --> 00:02:26.213
It's the locks.
They're different.

41
00:02:26.346 --> 00:02:27.682
-You see that?
-Oh. wow.

42
00:02:27.815 --> 00:02:30.752
Okay. so they broke
into this one.

43
00:02:30.885 --> 00:02:33.186
took the contents.
replaced the lock.

44
00:02:33.988 --> 00:02:35.322
The bank didn't even notice.

45
00:02:35.723 --> 00:02:38.760
-That's an archvillain move
right there.
-[chuckles]

46
00:02:39.127 --> 00:02:41.863
Hey. Price. Price.

47
00:02:41.996 --> 00:02:44.264
[whimpers] What now?

48
00:02:44.398 --> 00:02:46.934
This safe deposit box.
I need the name
and address of its owner.

49
00:02:47.068 --> 00:02:50.538
Oh. I am not permitted
to release that information

50
00:02:50.672 --> 00:02:52.239
without the client's approval.

51
00:02:52.674 --> 00:02:55.076
You know we're investigating
a robbery. right?

52
00:02:55.208 --> 00:02:57.045
I'm sorry. but it is policy.

53
00:02:57.512 --> 00:02:59.279
-Never mind.
-We'll get a warrant.

54
00:03:06.954 --> 00:03:10.992
[video narrator]
<i>Let us help you find</i>
<i>what you're longing for.</i>

55
00:03:11.425 --> 00:03:14.162
<i>your ideal life partner.</i>

56
00:03:15.063 --> 00:03:19.534
<i>Jennings Luxury.</i>
<i>For your happily ever after.</i>

57
00:03:19.901 --> 00:03:21.969
[Amanda] Whole lot
of powerful Atlanta names

58
00:03:22.103 --> 00:03:25.338
use this matchmaking service.
What ever happened
to just meeting people?

59
00:03:25.472 --> 00:03:26.708
You know. chance encounters?

60
00:03:26.841 --> 00:03:28.843
I've actually been
researching hermit life.

61
00:03:28.976 --> 00:03:31.311
It's a whole movement.
Want me to send you
some information? I can--

62
00:03:31.445 --> 00:03:32.880
-No.
-Get on with it.

63
00:03:33.246 --> 00:03:34.716
Fine.

64
00:03:34.849 --> 00:03:37.384
One perforating gunshot entered
the right arm back here.

65
00:03:37.518 --> 00:03:39.754
exited the front here.
Four more to his chest.

66
00:03:39.887 --> 00:03:41.622
So someone shot him
with his back turned.

67
00:03:41.756 --> 00:03:44.257
He spun around.
They finished it. plus some.

68
00:03:44.391 --> 00:03:45.626
This happened outside his home?

69
00:03:45.760 --> 00:03:48.062
No apparent robbery.
No witnesses.

70
00:03:48.428 --> 00:03:50.397
Could have been
a disgruntled client.

71
00:03:51.331 --> 00:03:53.701
[Faith]
All these women seem identical.

72
00:03:53.835 --> 00:03:56.137
Like to travel.
live an active lifestyle.

73
00:03:56.269 --> 00:03:58.873
Why are so many of them
event planners?

74
00:03:59.006 --> 00:04:00.373
They just throw parties?

75
00:04:00.508 --> 00:04:02.110
What is that?
Like a brand ambassador?

76
00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:04.377
-I thought that
was an influencer.
-Whatever the job is.

77
00:04:04.512 --> 00:04:07.782
it's vague enough they
probably don't get asked
too many follow-up questions.

78
00:04:07.915 --> 00:04:10.551
I do like that.
I can't have another man ask me

79
00:04:10.685 --> 00:04:13.353
to fix a parking ticket
when he finds out I am GBI.

80
00:04:13.487 --> 00:04:16.724
You telling these men
your government name
and where you work?

81
00:04:16.858 --> 00:04:18.993
-For the government?
-That's a good point.

82
00:04:19.127 --> 00:04:21.095
-[phone chimes]
-Okay.

83
00:04:21.229 --> 00:04:23.197
Ah! The business partner
is here.

84
00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:28.002
Ms. Summermann. we pulled
Mr. Jennings's phone records.

85
00:04:28.136 --> 00:04:31.172
He made several calls to you
in the hours before he died.

86
00:04:32.073 --> 00:04:34.474
Sawyer and I talked
all the time.

87
00:04:35.275 --> 00:04:36.544
Mostly business. [sighs]

88
00:04:36.677 --> 00:04:37.879
And we're friends.

89
00:04:38.012 --> 00:04:39.446
Well. I have to ask.

90
00:04:39.881 --> 00:04:42.116
last night. where were you
between 7:00 and 8:00?

91
00:04:42.250 --> 00:04:44.852
I take a 7:00 spin class.

92
00:04:44.986 --> 00:04:46.788
BLUEGYM in Piedmont.

93
00:04:46.921 --> 00:04:51.592
Did you and Mr. Jennings have
any disagreements lately?
Personal? Financial?

94
00:04:51.726 --> 00:04:52.927
None.

95
00:04:53.594 --> 00:04:56.864
I mean. I don't mean to
sound callous. but the company
has never been better.

96
00:04:56.998 --> 00:04:58.266
What about the members?

97
00:04:58.900 --> 00:05:01.269
Were any of them unhappy
with the service?

98
00:05:02.036 --> 00:05:05.807
If a date isn't a match.
we work with the client
to make it right.

99
00:05:06.941 --> 00:05:07.875
Just curious.

100
00:05:08.308 --> 00:05:11.913
you charge male clients
$50.000 for a membership.

101
00:05:12.046 --> 00:05:13.581
and women only pay five.

102
00:05:14.381 --> 00:05:15.917
Men aren't angry about that?

103
00:05:16.050 --> 00:05:20.320
It's standard practice in
high-end matchmaking services.

104
00:05:21.421 --> 00:05:25.626
If you weren't to charge
the women. it could seem
like prostitution too. huh?

105
00:05:27.862 --> 00:05:29.997
Yes. we charge a steep fee.

106
00:05:30.131 --> 00:05:35.570
but some people are willing
to pay any price to find
that one great love.

107
00:05:36.304 --> 00:05:41.108
My work is
bringing people together.
helping them find joy.

108
00:05:43.277 --> 00:05:46.914
Ms. Summermann. I'm gonna need
the contact information
for your clients.

109
00:05:47.048 --> 00:05:50.383
I hope you find the monster
that took Sawyer from us.

110
00:05:50.518 --> 00:05:55.990
And... maybe I can help you
find your joy.

111
00:06:00.460 --> 00:06:03.164
[♪ pop music playing
over speakers]

112
00:06:03.297 --> 00:06:08.102
I don't need your help
because I have a date.

113
00:06:09.270 --> 00:06:10.504
[phone chimes]

114
00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:18.145
"See you soon."

115
00:06:18.279 --> 00:06:22.482
"If I get a parking ticket.
can you help me out?"

116
00:06:24.151 --> 00:06:25.385
[sighs]

117
00:06:27.021 --> 00:06:28.189
"Sorry.

118
00:06:28.322 --> 00:06:31.525
Killed in the line of duty.
Reservation canceled."

119
00:06:31.659 --> 00:06:32.793
[message sent tone]

120
00:06:32.927 --> 00:06:34.662
And blocked.

121
00:06:35.830 --> 00:06:37.098
-Hey.
-[bartender] Yeah?

122
00:06:37.231 --> 00:06:42.469
Can I get a gin martini.
extra dirty. extra gin?

123
00:06:46.073 --> 00:06:47.108
[sighs]

124
00:06:54.181 --> 00:06:59.086
I don't wanna be that dude.
but I'm gonna be that dude.

125
00:07:00.453 --> 00:07:03.524
You are stunning.

126
00:07:05.359 --> 00:07:08.596
Any way you'd say yes
if I asked to sit with you?

127
00:07:09.697 --> 00:07:11.832
Everything you just said was

128
00:07:12.600 --> 00:07:14.302
so hypothetical.

129
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:16.103
[both laugh]

130
00:07:17.705 --> 00:07:19.307
Ouch.
Right. right. right. right.

131
00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:22.610
I-I should just ask. huh?

132
00:07:22.743 --> 00:07:23.978
Or you could just sit.

133
00:07:26.580 --> 00:07:29.383
-Great.
-You know. I'd say good.

134
00:07:29.517 --> 00:07:30.851
I don't know about great yet.

135
00:07:30.985 --> 00:07:34.722
When does this snark wear off?

136
00:07:34.855 --> 00:07:36.223
I'm just curious.

137
00:07:36.757 --> 00:07:37.992
This will help.

138
00:07:44.098 --> 00:07:45.232
I'm Malcolm.

139
00:07:45.366 --> 00:07:47.601
I didn't even ask
for your name. I'm sorry.

140
00:07:49.937 --> 00:07:51.072
Amanda.

141
00:07:51.639 --> 00:07:53.274
I'm an event planner.

142
00:07:53.407 --> 00:07:58.179
Okay. so about weather.
common interests.
world peace. no?

143
00:07:58.312 --> 00:08:00.081
You just jump right
to your job title.

144
00:08:00.214 --> 00:08:01.481
[chuckles]

145
00:08:01.615 --> 00:08:04.218
-You must be a Leo.
-I'm sorry. my bad.

146
00:08:04.352 --> 00:08:06.854
I assumed that
I was talking to a grown man.

147
00:08:07.288 --> 00:08:10.124
You know. I haven't met
an astrology buff since...

148
00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:13.027
high school.

149
00:08:14.095 --> 00:08:16.330
-[giggling]
-Oh. Ouch.

150
00:08:16.464 --> 00:08:17.798
[both chuckling]

151
00:08:17.932 --> 00:08:19.834
Did I just play myself?

152
00:08:20.534 --> 00:08:22.536
Let's have
this one drink and see.

153
00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:27.375
I can do that.

154
00:08:27.742 --> 00:08:30.211
[♪ "Ain't Nobody" playing]

155
00:08:30.344 --> 00:08:31.579
Cheers.

156
00:08:32.613 --> 00:08:35.449
You think I'm feisty?

157
00:08:35.583 --> 00:08:37.952
What?
You don't think you... [laughs]

158
00:08:38.085 --> 00:08:40.921
Okay. all right. you know what?
I'm-I'm so sorry.

159
00:08:41.055 --> 00:08:42.723
I was just kidding.
I was just kidding.

160
00:08:42.857 --> 00:08:45.593
You know what? It's fine.
because. yeah. I'm a Leo.

161
00:08:45.726 --> 00:08:46.727
so it's fine.

162
00:08:46.861 --> 00:08:48.229
-Mm-hmm.
-It's okay.

163
00:08:48.662 --> 00:08:50.164
I do feel bad though.

164
00:08:50.297 --> 00:08:53.334
We're keeping the waitstaff
here so late. [groans]

165
00:08:53.467 --> 00:08:54.503
[Malcolm scoffs]

166
00:08:55.069 --> 00:08:58.305
Sorry if this
is too forward. but...

167
00:08:59.974 --> 00:09:03.277
I do have a room here
at the hotel.

168
00:09:03.411 --> 00:09:07.014
♪ <i>And hope this night</i>
<i>Will last forever</i> ♪

169
00:09:07.148 --> 00:09:09.917
♪ <i>Oh. oh. oh. oh</i> ♪

170
00:09:10.051 --> 00:09:11.185
♪ <i>Ain't nobody</i> ♪

171
00:09:11.318 --> 00:09:12.319
♪ <i>Ain't nobody</i> ♪

172
00:09:12.453 --> 00:09:13.954
♪ <i>Loves me better</i> ♪

173
00:09:14.555 --> 00:09:17.224
-♪ <i>Makes me happy</i> ♪
-♪ <i>Makes me feel this way</i> ♪

174
00:09:17.358 --> 00:09:19.827
Okay. okay. maybe hold on.

175
00:09:19.960 --> 00:09:21.228
-Um...
-[sighs. clears throat]

176
00:09:21.362 --> 00:09:23.197
[stutters] I'm not saying stop.

177
00:09:23.330 --> 00:09:26.133
I'm just saying that
we've only known each other
for three hours. so...

178
00:09:26.267 --> 00:09:28.636
-Mm-hmm. Okay. Um. hmm.
-[clears throat] Yeah.

179
00:09:28.769 --> 00:09:30.505
-Medical issues?
-Diabetes.

180
00:09:30.638 --> 00:09:32.273
-Good to know.
-Allergies?

181
00:09:32.406 --> 00:09:34.408
-Wasp. Favorite movie?
<i>-Say Anything.</i>
Have you seen it?

182
00:09:34.543 --> 00:09:35.876
Uh. maybe a long time ago.

183
00:09:36.010 --> 00:09:38.045
Do you have any outstanding
parking tickets?

184
00:09:38.179 --> 00:09:39.280
I have a driver.

185
00:09:39.413 --> 00:09:40.581
Family? Where did you grow up?

186
00:09:40.714 --> 00:09:42.216
-You know what?
-Mm.

187
00:09:42.349 --> 00:09:44.151
-I think that is good enough.
-Okay.

188
00:09:44.285 --> 00:09:46.287
♪ <i>And a love so deep</i>
<i>We cannot measure</i> ♪

189
00:09:46.420 --> 00:09:48.722
-♪ <i>Ain't nobody</i> ♪
-♪ <i>Nobody</i> ♪

190
00:09:48.856 --> 00:09:53.994
-♪ <i>Loves me better</i> ♪
-♪ <i>That can make me</i>
<i>Feel this way</i> ♪

191
00:09:54.128 --> 00:09:55.930
♪ <i>Makes me feel this way</i> ♪

192
00:09:56.063 --> 00:09:57.898
-♪ <i>Ain't nobody</i> ♪
-♪ <i>Ain't nobody</i> ♪

193
00:09:58.032 --> 00:10:00.768
-♪ <i>Loves me better</i> ♪
-♪ <i>Nobody</i> ♪

194
00:10:00.901 --> 00:10:04.205
♪ <i>Ain't nobody</i>
<i>Loves me better</i> ♪

195
00:10:04.338 --> 00:10:06.240
♪ <i>Than you</i> ♪

196
00:10:06.373 --> 00:10:07.641
[breathing heavily]

197
00:10:07.775 --> 00:10:09.376
-Amanda.
-No.

198
00:10:09.511 --> 00:10:11.745
[♪ "Ain't Nobody" continues]

199
00:10:39.140 --> 00:10:40.941
Nice to meet you. Malcolm.

200
00:10:59.860 --> 00:11:01.695
[Malcolm]
The site sounds perfect.

201
00:11:03.898 --> 00:11:08.302
All right. Well. send me
the specs and we'll see
if we can make it work.

202
00:11:09.770 --> 00:11:11.005
All right.

203
00:11:12.273 --> 00:11:13.307
Bye.

204
00:11:14.108 --> 00:11:16.578
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

205
00:11:16.710 --> 00:11:18.179
-Hey.
-Hey.

206
00:11:22.149 --> 00:11:23.751
-Ooh. [chuckles]
-[giggles]

207
00:11:24.553 --> 00:11:26.687
I'm sorry. I just had
to take care of a few things.

208
00:11:26.820 --> 00:11:29.924
No. you're good.
You're very good.

209
00:11:31.859 --> 00:11:33.027
You know... [clears throat]

210
00:11:33.562 --> 00:11:35.262
...during our little Q and A
last night.

211
00:11:35.396 --> 00:11:38.098
I forgot
the most important question.

212
00:11:38.232 --> 00:11:39.266
Oh?

213
00:11:40.234 --> 00:11:43.605
Are you a coffee or tea person?

214
00:11:43.737 --> 00:11:46.740
So. I just got
a little of everything.

215
00:11:46.874 --> 00:11:52.012
You sure did. and I wish
that I would have taken that
apple tart to go last night.

216
00:11:52.146 --> 00:11:53.914
It would've been
amazing right now.

217
00:11:54.048 --> 00:11:57.284
Well. I can call down
and have the pastry chef
whip one up for you.

218
00:11:57.418 --> 00:12:00.589
[chuckles] I'm pretty sure
the restaurant's
not open this early.

219
00:12:01.021 --> 00:12:03.324
They'll do it for me.
It's my restaurant.

220
00:12:04.024 --> 00:12:06.628
[chuckles]
You know. that's cute.

221
00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:09.763
but the restaurant's connected
to the hotel. so...

222
00:12:09.897 --> 00:12:10.864
-It is.
-Hmm.

223
00:12:10.998 --> 00:12:13.067
I also own the hotel.

224
00:12:15.736 --> 00:12:16.971
-[chuckles]
-Hmm.

225
00:12:17.706 --> 00:12:19.840
"Hmm"?
Oh. you don't believe me?

226
00:12:19.974 --> 00:12:21.976
-I didn't say that.
-All right. look it up.

227
00:12:22.109 --> 00:12:23.444
The Quinton Atlanta.

228
00:12:23.578 --> 00:12:24.713
Oh. I know where we are.

229
00:12:24.845 --> 00:12:27.147
-Go ahead. I'll wait.
-[scoffs]

230
00:12:29.618 --> 00:12:30.851
Mm.

231
00:12:33.120 --> 00:12:35.856
-Oh. my God.
-Mm-hmm.

232
00:12:35.990 --> 00:12:38.259
You wouldn't believe
how many times
this has happened to me.

233
00:12:38.392 --> 00:12:43.163
Honestly.
if I accidentally sleep
with one more millionaire...

234
00:12:43.297 --> 00:12:44.331
Mm.

235
00:12:44.965 --> 00:12:46.534
-Well. look.
-Hmm?

236
00:12:47.134 --> 00:12:49.336
The kitchen started prepping
at 8:00--

237
00:12:49.470 --> 00:12:51.438
-Wait. wait. it's past 8:00?
-Yeah.

238
00:12:51.573 --> 00:12:53.541
-I gotta go.
-What? Wait. wait. wait.
Hey. hey. hey.

239
00:12:53.675 --> 00:12:55.577
sure. sure. all right. but...

240
00:12:56.076 --> 00:12:57.512
And when can I see you again?

241
00:12:58.345 --> 00:13:00.347
Actually. that's not
what I meant to ask.

242
00:13:00.481 --> 00:13:03.484
Can I see you tonight?

243
00:13:04.151 --> 00:13:07.187
Here. Amanda.
put in your number.

244
00:13:12.126 --> 00:13:14.562
-[elevator bell dings]
-[indistinct chatter]

245
00:13:18.767 --> 00:13:21.636
[Will]
...said she was angry crying.
Okay. cool. Thank you.

246
00:13:21.770 --> 00:13:24.673
Oh. hey!
Glad you could make it.

247
00:13:24.805 --> 00:13:28.275
Me? I've just been diligently
working while you were. what?

248
00:13:28.876 --> 00:13:30.811
Dancing with temptation.
were we?

249
00:13:30.944 --> 00:13:33.682
I held it down here
for months while you went
to go find yourself at...

250
00:13:33.814 --> 00:13:35.550
What was the name
of that place?

251
00:13:35.916 --> 00:13:36.917
Hypocrite. Tennessee?

252
00:13:37.051 --> 00:13:38.720
That lovely town
is Soddy-Daisy.

253
00:13:38.886 --> 00:13:40.387
And you're wearing
the same clothes as yesterday.

254
00:13:40.522 --> 00:13:42.489
Oh. shut up.
Nobody's gonna notice.

255
00:13:42.624 --> 00:13:45.225
Oh. Faith. why are you wearing
the same clothes
you wore yesterday?

256
00:13:45.359 --> 00:13:47.227
Can everybody stop worrying
about what I'm wearing?

257
00:13:47.361 --> 00:13:49.798
Oh. You had a date last night.

258
00:13:49.930 --> 00:13:51.633
[Will]
I wasn't gonna say anything.

259
00:13:51.766 --> 00:13:54.134
but I'm pretty sure
that's a bra strap
sticking out your purse.

260
00:13:54.769 --> 00:13:57.104
Oh. Lord. Please just tell me
he does not work
in this building.

261
00:13:57.237 --> 00:13:59.340
He doesn't even know
that I work in this building.

262
00:13:59.473 --> 00:14:02.309
so there you go. He thinks
I am an event planner.

263
00:14:02.443 --> 00:14:05.245
-Hmm. What name
did you use? Beyoncé?
-Mmm.

264
00:14:05.379 --> 00:14:06.480
Sasha?

265
00:14:07.247 --> 00:14:08.916
-Shakira?
-[clears throat]

266
00:14:09.049 --> 00:14:11.586
I always used Simone.
She was my old boss.

267
00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:12.787
Mmm.

268
00:14:12.920 --> 00:14:15.322
-What?
-I had to think fast.

269
00:14:15.456 --> 00:14:18.025
Faith Mitchell.
you did not use my name!

270
00:14:18.158 --> 00:14:19.728
No. that is not okay
and inappropriate.

271
00:14:19.860 --> 00:14:21.796
You were just talking
about my bra in my purse.

272
00:14:21.929 --> 00:14:23.163
And where's the lie?

273
00:14:23.798 --> 00:14:26.967
What did it sound like
when he whispered
my name in your ear?

274
00:14:27.101 --> 00:14:28.503
-Ew.
-Gross.

275
00:14:28.636 --> 00:14:31.573
[chuckles] Now. what's
your progress on this case?

276
00:14:31.706 --> 00:14:33.541
Sawyer Jennings's
credit card records show

277
00:14:33.675 --> 00:14:36.410
that he went
to a diner in Midtown
the night he was killed.

278
00:14:36.544 --> 00:14:38.613
Manager said that he was there
with a woman.

279
00:14:38.747 --> 00:14:40.080
She was angry crying.

280
00:14:40.214 --> 00:14:42.082
Was it Liv Summermann.
his business partner?

281
00:14:42.216 --> 00:14:45.252
Anna Martello. She used
a credit card to buy a drink
before Jennings arrived.

282
00:14:45.386 --> 00:14:46.855
Let's go pay her a visit.

283
00:14:46.987 --> 00:14:50.592
Wonderful idea.
Thank you. "Amanda <i>chiquita.</i> "

284
00:14:50.725 --> 00:14:51.659
That's "little Amanda."

285
00:14:51.793 --> 00:14:52.893
[chuckles]

286
00:14:53.595 --> 00:14:57.331
-I did this to myself.
-[giggles] Sure did.

287
00:15:01.034 --> 00:15:02.369
Sure you don't wanna sit?

288
00:15:02.504 --> 00:15:04.037
[sighing] No.
Standing's better for my back.

289
00:15:04.839 --> 00:15:08.543
Okay. Price said
First Peachtree Bank
lost 500.000 in cash.

290
00:15:08.676 --> 00:15:10.645
-It's not a bad haul. but...
-[sighs]

291
00:15:10.779 --> 00:15:12.946
...considering the equipment
these guys used to cut
into that vault.

292
00:15:13.080 --> 00:15:14.214
these guys are pros.

293
00:15:14.348 --> 00:15:16.049
-That's chump change to them.
-Yeah.

294
00:15:16.183 --> 00:15:19.554
unless what was in
the safe deposit box
was worth way more.

295
00:15:19.687 --> 00:15:23.290
You know. it'd be great
if the judge would respond
to my warrant request.

296
00:15:23.424 --> 00:15:24.726
You gotta work the clerk.

297
00:15:24.859 --> 00:15:27.227
I am working the clerk.
Let me see the photo.

298
00:15:29.163 --> 00:15:32.299
-That's the burger place
up on the corner?
-Yeah. pretty good camera.

299
00:15:32.433 --> 00:15:34.334
Must be why
they charge 30 bucks a burger.

300
00:15:34.468 --> 00:15:38.205
Oh. Black sedan.
no plates. no faces.

301
00:15:38.338 --> 00:15:41.208
The rear passenger
has a huge head.

302
00:15:43.711 --> 00:15:46.413
-That's not his head.
that's a mask.
-Animal mask.

303
00:15:46.548 --> 00:15:48.282
Oh. She shifted. I gotta sit.

304
00:15:48.415 --> 00:15:50.017
Oh. yeah. here. here.

305
00:15:50.752 --> 00:15:52.386
All right. So... [sighs]

306
00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:56.156
...I can add "animal mask"
to the search.

307
00:15:57.090 --> 00:15:59.326
Hey. look at that. That did it.

308
00:15:59.460 --> 00:16:02.764
Three similar robberies.
the last three years.

309
00:16:02.897 --> 00:16:06.300
Nashville. Chicago. Oakland.

310
00:16:06.433 --> 00:16:08.202
-Same crew?
-It's hard to say.

311
00:16:08.335 --> 00:16:11.138
These similar robberies were
all of cash management
warehouses

312
00:16:11.271 --> 00:16:13.708
and they made off
with 20 to 30 million each.

313
00:16:13.842 --> 00:16:15.375
But only half a mil from here.

314
00:16:15.510 --> 00:16:18.212
They really wanted what
was in that safe deposit box.

315
00:16:18.979 --> 00:16:22.249
Ormewood. I hear you got
X-ray vision. What kind
of underwear am I wearing now?

316
00:16:22.382 --> 00:16:24.284
That's a trick question.
Don't answer.

317
00:16:24.418 --> 00:16:25.787
Don't mock my superpowers.

318
00:16:25.920 --> 00:16:27.689
Can you fly? Can he fly?

319
00:16:27.822 --> 00:16:31.191
Franklin. get in here! Now!

320
00:16:34.094 --> 00:16:35.362
Um. what do I do?

321
00:16:35.496 --> 00:16:37.565
Oh. Now you want me
to be clairvoyant?

322
00:16:37.699 --> 00:16:39.032
[smacks lips] Too late.

323
00:16:39.166 --> 00:16:41.001
[sighs]

324
00:16:41.703 --> 00:16:42.737
Good luck.

325
00:16:47.976 --> 00:16:49.209
[Franklin] Oh.

326
00:16:51.646 --> 00:16:52.780
What's up. Cap?

327
00:16:52.914 --> 00:16:54.348
[groans]

328
00:16:56.183 --> 00:16:57.986
I need your help.

329
00:16:58.118 --> 00:16:59.353
Who is that under the tarp?

330
00:16:59.486 --> 00:17:02.757
It's a surprise
for Polaski's kid.

331
00:17:05.092 --> 00:17:06.026
Got her a stroller.

332
00:17:06.159 --> 00:17:07.361
Oh. that is not a stroller.

333
00:17:07.494 --> 00:17:09.229
Oh. it will be
after we put it together.

334
00:17:09.363 --> 00:17:12.065
That's crazy.
Sounded like you said "we."

335
00:17:13.601 --> 00:17:15.904
Fine. Where's
the instruction manual?

336
00:17:16.036 --> 00:17:19.072
Did the cavemen need a manual
when they created fire?

337
00:17:19.206 --> 00:17:20.942
They got ate by dinosaurs.

338
00:17:21.074 --> 00:17:23.645
Did the Mesopotamians
need a manual when
they invented the wheel?

339
00:17:23.778 --> 00:17:25.479
They invented it
to outrun tuberculosis.

340
00:17:25.613 --> 00:17:27.515
When Thomas Edison
invented the lightbulb.

341
00:17:27.649 --> 00:17:29.651
-he didn't have a manual--
-Look. I'ma stop you
right there.

342
00:17:29.784 --> 00:17:31.920
He stole that
from Lewis Latimer.
and you threw away the manual.

343
00:17:32.052 --> 00:17:33.387
Yes. I did.

344
00:17:34.121 --> 00:17:35.723
[sighs]

345
00:17:35.857 --> 00:17:38.325
So. let's see if
we can get a better shot
of our getaway car.

346
00:17:38.458 --> 00:17:41.763
These are from a drugstore
a mile east of the bank.

347
00:17:42.229 --> 00:17:43.463
Black sedan.

348
00:17:44.164 --> 00:17:47.001
-What is that pattern
in the rear window?
-[Michael] The spots?

349
00:17:47.134 --> 00:17:49.069
-Yeah.
-That's a cheetah.

350
00:17:51.438 --> 00:17:53.473
-I gotta pee. Walk with me?
-Yeah.

351
00:17:54.341 --> 00:17:57.411
All right.
there's an arm in this photo.

352
00:17:57.545 --> 00:17:59.246
[Michael] Is that a tattoo?

353
00:17:59.714 --> 00:18:00.882
Could be a mole.

354
00:18:01.015 --> 00:18:02.684
-It could be
a tattoo of a mole.
-Mmm.

355
00:18:02.817 --> 00:18:04.284
Hey. Mishi's froggy.

356
00:18:05.185 --> 00:18:08.656
-Come again?
-Yeah. Mishi.
she's an ATL tattoo legend.

357
00:18:08.790 --> 00:18:10.625
Yeah. that frog's
her signature.

358
00:18:10.992 --> 00:18:14.261
How can you not know Mishi?
What have you been doing
with your lives?

359
00:18:14.394 --> 00:18:15.964
-[Angie chuckles]
-Not getting arrested.

360
00:18:16.096 --> 00:18:17.932
-Oh. okay.
-Thank you. sir.

361
00:18:18.900 --> 00:18:24.204
-Uh. Mishi.
heard she's a legend.
-Oh.

362
00:18:26.106 --> 00:18:29.744
Well. people pay Jennings
big money to find
their perfect life partner.

363
00:18:29.877 --> 00:18:32.312
all the while
he's in a toxic relationship
with Anna Martello.

364
00:18:32.446 --> 00:18:35.917
The number of gunshots
does point to his death
being a crime of passion.

365
00:18:36.517 --> 00:18:39.020
-Speaking of passion--
-Don't you say passion!

366
00:18:39.186 --> 00:18:41.421
I won't kiss and tell.
and I don't need
any dating advice.

367
00:18:41.556 --> 00:18:44.792
Okay. you're right. I mean.
it's obvious you got this
all under control. Amanda.

368
00:18:44.926 --> 00:18:47.895
Uh. what is there
to have under control?
It was one night. that's all.

369
00:18:48.029 --> 00:18:49.162
You know. I agree.

370
00:18:49.296 --> 00:18:50.598
Not everything
has to be so serious.

371
00:18:50.732 --> 00:18:53.333
Someone told me that recently.
and they...

372
00:18:53.467 --> 00:18:55.302
she... they have a point.

373
00:18:55.435 --> 00:18:57.471
Was it Ava?
Was Ava the they/she/they?

374
00:18:57.605 --> 00:18:59.139
By the way.
I knew that you slept with her.

375
00:18:59.272 --> 00:19:01.009
I just know
how to mind my business.

376
00:19:01.141 --> 00:19:02.376
Mm-hmm.

377
00:19:03.778 --> 00:19:05.178
Anna Martello.

378
00:19:06.213 --> 00:19:07.381
[Anna] No. no. no. no.

379
00:19:07.515 --> 00:19:09.017
[Will] Hey. GBI. Hey. Anna!

380
00:19:09.149 --> 00:19:10.952
-Ms. Martello.
don't run. We just...
-[Anna] Help!

381
00:19:11.085 --> 00:19:12.854
-...need to ask you
a few questions about...
-[Anna] Help me!

382
00:19:12.987 --> 00:19:14.589
Please don't. [cries]

383
00:19:14.722 --> 00:19:17.592
[sobs] He sent you to kill me.
didn't he?

384
00:19:18.126 --> 00:19:19.093
Who?

385
00:19:19.226 --> 00:19:21.529
[panting]

386
00:19:26.199 --> 00:19:27.568
I'm being followed.

387
00:19:28.603 --> 00:19:30.404
I know I sound paranoid.
but it's true.

388
00:19:30.538 --> 00:19:33.306
I've been staying with
my sister. I came back
to get some clothes.

389
00:19:33.440 --> 00:19:35.109
and you were at my door and...

390
00:19:36.176 --> 00:19:38.780
I thought he sent you to
kill me like he killed Sawyer.

391
00:19:39.312 --> 00:19:41.248
I need you to give me a name.

392
00:19:42.984 --> 00:19:44.217
[sighs]

393
00:19:46.020 --> 00:19:47.387
Brody Evans.

394
00:19:48.422 --> 00:19:50.390
Three weeks ago.
we went on a date.

395
00:19:51.025 --> 00:19:52.093
[scoffs] A match.

396
00:19:52.225 --> 00:19:54.361
-Through Jennings Luxury?
-Yeah.

397
00:19:55.362 --> 00:19:56.864
Brody's family is old money.

398
00:19:56.998 --> 00:19:59.534
He owns his own tech firm.

399
00:19:59.667 --> 00:20:01.301
We got drinks. [sighs]

400
00:20:01.435 --> 00:20:02.637
I blacked out.

401
00:20:03.604 --> 00:20:05.305
Or that's what
Brody said happened.

402
00:20:05.439 --> 00:20:06.808
Were you...

403
00:20:08.943 --> 00:20:09.977
hurt?

404
00:20:13.047 --> 00:20:16.517
Brody threatened me
if I talked to the police...

405
00:20:18.052 --> 00:20:19.252
And his family?

406
00:20:20.021 --> 00:20:23.524
I can't afford that-that fight.
[sniffles]

407
00:20:26.527 --> 00:20:29.630
But the one thing I could do...

408
00:20:31.264 --> 00:20:34.702
was make sure other women
weren't handed over
to that creep.

409
00:20:35.703 --> 00:20:37.705
I told Sawyer the day
after it happened.

410
00:20:37.839 --> 00:20:42.844
He promised me that Brody
would be dropped as a client.

411
00:20:43.911 --> 00:20:45.580
This is three weeks ago?

412
00:20:47.081 --> 00:20:50.417
Anna. you saw Sawyer
one hour before he was killed.

413
00:20:50.551 --> 00:20:54.188
There was a witness
at the diner that overheard
you yelling at him. Why?

414
00:20:54.321 --> 00:20:57.959
Because Jennings Luxury
posted photos from
their monthly mixer.

415
00:20:58.693 --> 00:21:01.996
I wasn't invited but Brody was.

416
00:21:02.830 --> 00:21:04.264
He was smiling.

417
00:21:04.397 --> 00:21:08.268
He had his arm wrapped around
some poor woman. I was livid.

418
00:21:08.401 --> 00:21:10.337
What was Sawyer's response?

419
00:21:10.872 --> 00:21:12.305
He didn't know.

420
00:21:14.175 --> 00:21:15.843
I believed him.

421
00:21:17.979 --> 00:21:20.248
So. he called Brody.

422
00:21:20.380 --> 00:21:21.883
While you were at the diner?

423
00:21:22.016 --> 00:21:23.350
Right in front of me.

424
00:21:23.483 --> 00:21:25.019
He said he knew
about the assault

425
00:21:25.452 --> 00:21:28.923
and that he would tell
everyone in Atlanta
that Brody was a monster.

426
00:21:31.058 --> 00:21:32.794
-[♪ hip-hop music playing]
-[needles buzzing]

427
00:21:32.927 --> 00:21:34.929
I can put you
on Mishi's wait-list.

428
00:21:35.062 --> 00:21:38.065
How's April...

429
00:21:39.967 --> 00:21:40.935
2028?

430
00:21:41.068 --> 00:21:43.303
-For a frog?
-Yeah.

431
00:21:44.972 --> 00:21:46.774
Mishi. Hi.

432
00:21:46.908 --> 00:21:49.710
Detective Polaski.
This is Detective Ormewood.

433
00:21:50.377 --> 00:21:51.311
We spoke.

434
00:21:51.444 --> 00:21:53.446
That's a lot of canvas.

435
00:21:55.283 --> 00:21:57.084
-Thank you.
-You want to show her
the photo?

436
00:21:57.218 --> 00:21:58.451
Yep.

437
00:22:00.555 --> 00:22:01.789
It's mine.

438
00:22:02.223 --> 00:22:03.758
Photo's crap.

439
00:22:05.358 --> 00:22:06.727
See here.

440
00:22:06.861 --> 00:22:09.630
-this is my signature
on the leaf.
-Great.

441
00:22:09.764 --> 00:22:11.699
We're going to need his name
and contact information

442
00:22:11.833 --> 00:22:13.000
if you have that on file.

443
00:22:13.134 --> 00:22:14.735
Ooh. I'm discreet.

444
00:22:14.869 --> 00:22:17.004
No paperwork.
cash and crypto only.

445
00:22:19.040 --> 00:22:21.876
You didn't happen to do this
other tattoo of his. did you?

446
00:22:22.009 --> 00:22:25.646
[scoffs]
I don't do mom tattoos.

447
00:22:26.747 --> 00:22:29.116
Well. look at that.
He has a mom.

448
00:22:30.051 --> 00:22:32.452
My client was enjoying
a concert at City Stage.

449
00:22:32.587 --> 00:22:36.324
-My boy Jelly Roll.
Great seats.
-According to phone records.

450
00:22:36.456 --> 00:22:40.595
you were one of the last people
Sawyer Jennings talked to
before he died.

451
00:22:41.461 --> 00:22:42.730
What did you two talk about?

452
00:22:42.864 --> 00:22:44.665
He was following up
to see how a date went.

453
00:22:45.032 --> 00:22:47.869
I pay top dollar.
so they want to keep me happy.

454
00:22:48.569 --> 00:22:50.403
I'm still looking
for my Amal Clooney.

455
00:22:50.538 --> 00:22:51.939
She's so exotic.

456
00:22:53.107 --> 00:22:55.343
Now. was the follow-up part
of that phone call

457
00:22:55.475 --> 00:23:00.114
before or after Mr. Jennings
threatened to expose you
for date-raping Anna Martello?

458
00:23:00.248 --> 00:23:01.916
Oh. come on.

459
00:23:02.049 --> 00:23:04.051
My client has
an alibi for the night
of Mr. Jennings's death.

460
00:23:04.185 --> 00:23:06.587
That's why we're here.
If some random woman
wants to accuse him--

461
00:23:06.721 --> 00:23:09.156
You can say her name.
Anna Martello.

462
00:23:09.290 --> 00:23:12.693
Unless she wants
to provide evidence
and bring a formal complaint.

463
00:23:12.827 --> 00:23:14.795
you're not to harass
my client again.

464
00:23:18.699 --> 00:23:20.167
What time was that concert?

465
00:23:21.335 --> 00:23:23.470
7:00. I left around midnight.

466
00:23:23.604 --> 00:23:24.739
You sure?

467
00:23:25.539 --> 00:23:29.010
I'm asking because Atlanta's
the most surveilled city
in the nation.

468
00:23:32.580 --> 00:23:35.149
I'ma scour through every bit
of that footage.

469
00:23:35.983 --> 00:23:40.755
Follow your every step
to find a hole in your alibi.

470
00:23:41.589 --> 00:23:43.057
We're done here.

471
00:23:46.694 --> 00:23:48.461
[Faith] Brody's scum.

472
00:23:48.596 --> 00:23:50.631
Why do people
who have money think
they can do whatever they want?

473
00:23:50.765 --> 00:23:52.432
Because they usually can.

474
00:23:53.801 --> 00:23:56.971
You know. did Sawyer's partner
mention the assault
when you interviewed her?

475
00:23:57.104 --> 00:24:00.675
No. she was too busy calling me
a true love skeptic.

476
00:24:01.575 --> 00:24:02.710
But she's not wrong.

477
00:24:02.843 --> 00:24:04.378
-Okay. you know what?
-[giggles]

478
00:24:04.512 --> 00:24:06.113
[phone rings]

479
00:24:06.847 --> 00:24:08.349
Hey. this is Amanda.

480
00:24:08.481 --> 00:24:09.583
Hi.

481
00:24:10.151 --> 00:24:12.153
Sounds good.
I will see you there.

482
00:24:12.286 --> 00:24:15.156
You know. sooner or later
you have to tell that man
your real name.

483
00:24:15.856 --> 00:24:17.992
I am protecting my peace.

484
00:24:18.125 --> 00:24:21.896
Look. if things
get serious with Malcolm.
I will tell him the truth.

485
00:24:22.029 --> 00:24:23.064
Cross my heart.

486
00:24:25.066 --> 00:24:26.567
[scoffs]

487
00:24:26.701 --> 00:24:29.236
Come on. Doreen.
I need Judge Earhart
to sign that warrant.

488
00:24:30.037 --> 00:24:32.406
Yeah. the safe deposit box.
you remembered.

489
00:24:33.341 --> 00:24:36.811
Well. can you move it
to the top of his pile?

490
00:24:38.579 --> 00:24:40.147
Yeah? You promise?

491
00:24:40.681 --> 00:24:42.383
Oh. You're the best.

492
00:24:42.516 --> 00:24:43.784
Hey. you still like
those Samoas?

493
00:24:43.918 --> 00:24:46.988
I got some for ya.
Four boxes on me.

494
00:24:48.222 --> 00:24:49.757
Thanks. Doreen.

495
00:24:49.890 --> 00:24:51.692
-Wow. you really are
working the clerk.
-Told ya.

496
00:24:51.826 --> 00:24:54.462
So. what's going on
with the mystery of
Cheetah Mask's mom?

497
00:24:54.595 --> 00:24:58.065
Well. don't want to brag. but.
um. I did cross reference women

498
00:24:58.199 --> 00:25:00.868
with her birth date.
death date and initials.

499
00:25:01.002 --> 00:25:03.070
which has led me to...
Guess how many moms.

500
00:25:03.838 --> 00:25:05.706
-Drumroll. please.
-Oh.

501
00:25:08.209 --> 00:25:09.243
One.

502
00:25:09.977 --> 00:25:11.545
Great.
Let's go pick up her son.

503
00:25:11.679 --> 00:25:13.481
Uh. not so fast.
She has ten kids.

504
00:25:13.614 --> 00:25:15.616
[grunts] My womb aches
for this woman.

505
00:25:21.055 --> 00:25:23.724
Franklin. what's going on
with you and Heller?

506
00:25:23.858 --> 00:25:25.426
You know. it's ugly in there.

507
00:25:25.559 --> 00:25:27.428
-[opens can]
-But it's for the good.

508
00:25:27.561 --> 00:25:28.796
[gulps]

509
00:25:36.037 --> 00:25:40.041
Hey. you said. uh. 7:00. right?

510
00:25:40.174 --> 00:25:42.843
-Where is everybody?
-[Malcolm] Yeah.
it's kind of weird. huh?

511
00:25:42.977 --> 00:25:45.813
I-I hope you don't mind.
I preordered.

512
00:25:46.347 --> 00:25:50.184
Wait. this is
the apple tart tatin
from the restaurant.

513
00:25:51.252 --> 00:25:52.319
Mm-hmm.

514
00:25:53.587 --> 00:25:56.390
Malcolm. did you rent out
this entire theater?

515
00:25:57.491 --> 00:26:00.394
-Yeah.
Is it too much? [chuckles]
-[chuckles]

516
00:26:00.529 --> 00:26:03.064
I mean. I'm into it.

517
00:26:03.631 --> 00:26:04.732
[chuckles]

518
00:26:04.865 --> 00:26:08.102
Listen.
I-I know it's early but...

519
00:26:09.770 --> 00:26:11.205
how this feels...

520
00:26:13.140 --> 00:26:15.142
I just want to see
where this can go.

521
00:26:21.348 --> 00:26:24.251
-[chuckles]
-[whispers]
What are we watching?

522
00:26:24.752 --> 00:26:27.088
Shh. It's a surprise.

523
00:26:27.221 --> 00:26:30.458
[Corey] <i>...long. and then</i>
<i>he writes. "You're a real</i>
<i>live wire. Love Mr. Carroll."</i>

524
00:26:30.591 --> 00:26:32.293
<i>You know. it's all so phony.</i>

525
00:26:32.426 --> 00:26:34.695
[DC] <i>He wants to leave things</i>
<i>on a good note.</i>

526
00:26:34.829 --> 00:26:37.998
[Corey] <i>Well. when Mr. Carroll</i>
<i>uses the word love.</i>
I look for a new word.

527
00:26:38.132 --> 00:26:39.467
-[chuckles]
<i>-</i> [DC] <i>Lloyd.</i>

528
00:26:39.934 --> 00:26:42.269
[Diane] <i>He lied to me.</i>
<i>He lied to everybody.</i>

529
00:26:43.070 --> 00:26:44.738
<i>I just left home.</i>

530
00:26:48.409 --> 00:26:50.044
<i>I need you.</i>

531
00:26:50.177 --> 00:26:52.012
-Oh. Wait. wait.
This is my favorite part.
-What. what?

532
00:26:52.146 --> 00:26:53.280
Okay.

533
00:26:53.414 --> 00:26:55.149
<i>Everything else</i>
<i>means nothing to me.</i>

534
00:26:56.817 --> 00:26:58.219
<i>I love you.</i>

535
00:26:58.352 --> 00:27:00.788
<i>How many more times</i>
<i>do I have to say it?</i>

536
00:27:05.693 --> 00:27:07.294
<i>I need you.</i>

537
00:27:17.972 --> 00:27:20.174
[elevator bell dings]

538
00:27:20.641 --> 00:27:22.577
-Oh.
-Good catch.

539
00:27:22.710 --> 00:27:24.546
We got to go. Eat that.

540
00:27:24.678 --> 00:27:27.348
Ooh. You took a change
of clothes with you
this time. You're learning.

541
00:27:27.481 --> 00:27:31.185
Can you please stop talking
about my private.
personal. private life?

542
00:27:31.553 --> 00:27:32.753
Fine.

543
00:27:32.887 --> 00:27:34.688
Brody Evans' alibi checked out.

544
00:27:34.822 --> 00:27:38.492
His. uh. smarmy face was
all over the concert jumbotron
the whole night.

545
00:27:38.627 --> 00:27:40.461
We need to link it
to Jennings' business partner.

546
00:27:40.595 --> 00:27:42.496
If Sawyer knew about
Brody Evans assaulting Anna.

547
00:27:42.631 --> 00:27:44.932
I don't believe for one second
that Liv didn't know too.

548
00:27:45.065 --> 00:27:48.702
Her spin class instructor
said Liv swiped a card on
the bike at the start of class.

549
00:27:48.836 --> 00:27:50.437
Maybe she snuck out.

550
00:27:50.572 --> 00:27:52.373
[elevator bell dings]

551
00:27:54.408 --> 00:27:55.442
[Angie clears throat]

552
00:28:00.114 --> 00:28:01.583
Well. look who it is.

553
00:28:02.082 --> 00:28:04.451
For two nights in a row.
you don't sleep at the house.

554
00:28:05.219 --> 00:28:06.787
I'm not prorating your rent.
you know?

555
00:28:06.921 --> 00:28:09.558
Can everybody stop
minding my business. please?

556
00:28:09.990 --> 00:28:12.293
[elevator buzzing]

557
00:28:12.426 --> 00:28:14.228
Oh. excuse me.

558
00:28:15.696 --> 00:28:18.132
-Franklin.
where's your sidearm?
-Wouldn't you like to know?

559
00:28:18.265 --> 00:28:20.034
Hey. did you get the warrant
for the safe deposit box?

560
00:28:20.167 --> 00:28:21.969
-What box?
-He's talking to us.

561
00:28:22.102 --> 00:28:24.038
A homicide at a bank heist.

562
00:28:24.171 --> 00:28:26.373
We're on our way
to go question the owner of
the safe deposit box right now.

563
00:28:26.508 --> 00:28:27.942
Okay. Superhero.

564
00:28:29.544 --> 00:28:30.911
How you feeling. Mama?

565
00:28:31.045 --> 00:28:33.280
Good. Yeah. really good.

566
00:28:33.414 --> 00:28:34.848
-Can I?
-Yeah.

567
00:28:35.816 --> 00:28:37.151
Hi. baby.

568
00:28:37.284 --> 00:28:39.320
[whispers]
It's Aunty Faith. Hi.

569
00:28:39.453 --> 00:28:40.754
[chuckles]

570
00:28:41.656 --> 00:28:43.625
-Hi.
-[elevator bell dings]

571
00:28:43.757 --> 00:28:44.925
Oh.

572
00:28:45.059 --> 00:28:46.794
-'Kay.
-Oh. Okay.

573
00:28:48.963 --> 00:28:50.798
"Wyatt Fernsby."

574
00:28:52.534 --> 00:28:54.835
He only had
the safe deposit box
a couple months.

575
00:28:54.969 --> 00:28:56.904
[sighs] Safe just don't mean
what it used to.

576
00:28:57.037 --> 00:28:59.139
That elevator thing was weird.
right? With Trent?

577
00:28:59.273 --> 00:29:03.210
Yeah. I'm fine. But you know
what really seems to help
is not talking about it.

578
00:29:03.344 --> 00:29:04.378
Thank you.

579
00:29:06.480 --> 00:29:07.815
[Fernsby coughs]

580
00:29:09.718 --> 00:29:11.819
-Mr. Fernsby?
-Oh. crap.

581
00:29:12.587 --> 00:29:13.622
APD.

582
00:29:13.787 --> 00:29:15.155
[Fernsby coughs]

583
00:29:15.289 --> 00:29:16.924
-I got him. I got him.
-Okay. I'll get an ambulance.

584
00:29:17.057 --> 00:29:19.628
[Fernsby coughing]

585
00:29:19.760 --> 00:29:23.264
Hey. yeah. Yeah. get an EMS.
You see my location.

586
00:29:23.831 --> 00:29:25.199
His vitals are stable.

587
00:29:25.332 --> 00:29:27.669
You have about five minutes.
He needs to rest.

588
00:29:27.801 --> 00:29:29.504
Okay. Thank you.

589
00:29:31.506 --> 00:29:33.474
Hey. Mr. Fernsby.

590
00:29:33.608 --> 00:29:36.277
we need to ask you some
questions about the contents
of that safe deposit box.

591
00:29:36.410 --> 00:29:39.213
You're aware that it was stolen
from First Peachtree Bank?

592
00:29:41.348 --> 00:29:45.185
Listen. someone was killed
during the robbery.

593
00:29:45.319 --> 00:29:47.722
We're trying to figure this out
before anyone else gets hurt.

594
00:29:47.888 --> 00:29:49.189
You can talk to us.

595
00:29:51.258 --> 00:29:55.796
I work for
Biosentia Pharmaceuticals.

596
00:29:57.264 --> 00:30:02.036
I was told to shred some
documents but I kept a copy.

597
00:30:02.704 --> 00:30:04.539
It was my insurance policy.

598
00:30:04.673 --> 00:30:06.240
That's what was in the box?

599
00:30:06.373 --> 00:30:08.510
Someone from the company must
have found out I took them.

600
00:30:09.810 --> 00:30:12.413
Do you understand what
these people will do to me?

601
00:30:12.547 --> 00:30:15.082
That's why you wanted
to end it yourself?

602
00:30:18.052 --> 00:30:22.489
Look. we need you
to tell us exactly what's
in those documents.

603
00:30:22.923 --> 00:30:25.225
I'm not saying anything
without a lawyer.

604
00:30:26.728 --> 00:30:31.098
Well. Wyatt Fernsby's lawyer
wants to strike a deal
with the DA.

605
00:30:32.199 --> 00:30:34.068
-What is he hiding?
-Yeah. no kidding.

606
00:30:34.201 --> 00:30:37.806
Definitely not what
I was expecting for
my first day back in the field.

607
00:30:37.938 --> 00:30:39.708
Surprise!

608
00:30:39.840 --> 00:30:41.676
Oho! Wow.

609
00:30:41.810 --> 00:30:45.479
Congratulations. Polaski.
You and that doc
are gonna have some kid.

610
00:30:46.815 --> 00:30:49.350
Ooh. Mmm.

611
00:30:50.552 --> 00:30:51.720
It wasn't me.

612
00:30:51.852 --> 00:30:54.488
Oh. It's all right.
It's all good.
[grunts]

613
00:30:54.622 --> 00:30:57.424
Thank you. That's...
[chuckles] ...really...

614
00:30:57.958 --> 00:30:59.761
It's very thoughtful of you.

615
00:30:59.893 --> 00:31:01.195
[Heller grunting]

616
00:31:01.328 --> 00:31:02.996
-You all right. Cap?
-Yeah. I'm all right.

617
00:31:03.130 --> 00:31:04.532
I'm great. [sighs]

618
00:31:04.666 --> 00:31:07.368
We're gonna get this worked out
and then we're...

619
00:31:07.501 --> 00:31:10.337
We'll get it back to you in...
[clicks tongue]
...tip-top shape.

620
00:31:10.971 --> 00:31:12.574
-We?
-Yeah. we.

621
00:31:12.707 --> 00:31:14.743
-Come on.
He ain't got no manual.
-Thank you. Cap.

622
00:31:14.875 --> 00:31:16.377
[Heller]
Why'd you tell 'em that?

623
00:31:16.511 --> 00:31:19.246
You ain't got no manual. That's
why I told her. No. Uh-uh.

624
00:31:19.380 --> 00:31:21.516
-You know we got
to take this to Amanda.
-Oh. I know.

625
00:31:21.649 --> 00:31:23.752
Why? 'Cause you can read
my mind? 'Cause you have ESP?

626
00:31:23.884 --> 00:31:25.219
-I mean. I do.
-[scoffs]

627
00:31:25.352 --> 00:31:28.322
But also because
our "murder at an ATM" case

628
00:31:28.455 --> 00:31:30.157
just turned into
a corporate espionage plot.

629
00:31:30.290 --> 00:31:35.229
-So. technically
we need the GBI.
-Yeah.

630
00:31:39.967 --> 00:31:43.070
The spin instructor said that
Liv was definitely here
when the class ended.

631
00:31:43.203 --> 00:31:45.339
She was yelling goodbye
and waving both of her hands

632
00:31:45.472 --> 00:31:48.208
like one of those
blow-up things at
the used car dealership.

633
00:31:48.342 --> 00:31:52.246
Hmm. Well. she made a show of
leaving to establish her alibi.

634
00:31:52.379 --> 00:31:53.313
-Yeah.
-"Hey. look at me.

635
00:31:53.447 --> 00:31:54.783
I've been here the whole time."

636
00:31:54.915 --> 00:31:56.551
It's dark in those studios.

637
00:31:56.684 --> 00:31:58.653
No one would notice
if she disappeared for a while.

638
00:31:58.787 --> 00:32:02.423
Only thing is.
parking lot attendant
said Liv's car never left.

639
00:32:02.891 --> 00:32:05.426
And Sawyer's house
is almost three miles away.

640
00:32:05.560 --> 00:32:08.730
She knew not to call a car.
Too easy to trace.

641
00:32:08.863 --> 00:32:10.164
Maybe she ran.

642
00:32:10.598 --> 00:32:13.200
Six miles plus the adrenaline
of killing Sawyer.

643
00:32:13.735 --> 00:32:16.136
then jumping back
on a spin bike? No.

644
00:32:16.738 --> 00:32:19.473
People would've noticed her
huffing and puffing.

645
00:32:20.174 --> 00:32:23.210
Or she didn't go on foot.

646
00:32:27.314 --> 00:32:29.950
-All right.
-[beeps]

647
00:32:31.084 --> 00:32:32.219
All right. I'll time you.

648
00:32:32.352 --> 00:32:34.421
-Okay. Ready. set--
-Hold on.

649
00:32:35.590 --> 00:32:36.925
[grunts]

650
00:32:37.057 --> 00:32:39.092
-What are you doing?
-Here.

651
00:32:39.226 --> 00:32:41.830
-Fine. Okay. [sighs]
-Hmm.

652
00:32:41.962 --> 00:32:42.897
-You need help?
-Nope.

653
00:32:43.030 --> 00:32:44.833
Okay. You sure?

654
00:32:44.965 --> 00:32:45.999
Yes.

655
00:32:46.400 --> 00:32:48.235
-How do I look?
-Good.

656
00:32:48.368 --> 00:32:50.037
-Okay. Um...
-[phone chimes]

657
00:32:51.940 --> 00:32:53.273
Eduardo. read text.

658
00:32:53.407 --> 00:32:57.745
<i>Text from Ava.</i>
<i>"Hey. sexy. send me a selfie?"</i>

659
00:32:58.580 --> 00:33:02.149
-Um... One second.
-Uh-huh.

660
00:33:03.918 --> 00:33:06.754
Oh. Will. She is not talking
about that kind of selfie.

661
00:33:08.121 --> 00:33:09.591
What do you mean?

662
00:33:10.123 --> 00:33:12.159
Oh. Oh!

663
00:33:12.292 --> 00:33:13.728
Oh. my. Really?

664
00:33:15.162 --> 00:33:17.264
That's quite forward. Um...

665
00:33:18.232 --> 00:33:20.067
-I'll respond to her later.
-Okay.

666
00:33:20.200 --> 00:33:22.837
-Shall we start?
-And go.

667
00:33:22.971 --> 00:33:24.171
Bye.

668
00:33:24.304 --> 00:33:25.907
[♪ "Summer Streets" playing]

669
00:33:26.039 --> 00:33:28.510
♪ <i>New kicks get wrecked</i>
<i>When we start to skate</i> ♪

670
00:33:28.643 --> 00:33:30.845
♪ <i>Summertime</i>
<i>Feel the windows open</i> ♪

671
00:33:30.979 --> 00:33:34.214
♪ <i>Feel good</i>
<i>In the warm breeze</i> ♪

672
00:33:34.348 --> 00:33:36.885
♪ <i>Summertime</i>
<i>eel the windows open</i> ♪

673
00:33:37.017 --> 00:33:39.521
♪ <i>Let your wings fly free</i> ♪

674
00:33:39.654 --> 00:33:41.990
♪ <i>You've been on my mind</i> ♪

675
00:33:42.122 --> 00:33:47.127
♪ <i>And I am hoping</i>
<i>You'll come run down</i>
<i>The sun with me</i> ♪

676
00:33:47.261 --> 00:33:49.697
♪ <i>Run down the sun with me</i> ♪

677
00:33:56.871 --> 00:33:58.105
[♪ song ends]

678
00:33:59.339 --> 00:34:00.575
Here we are.

679
00:34:02.142 --> 00:34:07.281
Bang. bang. bang. bang. bang.

680
00:34:11.351 --> 00:34:15.790
Now. would Liv head back
the way she came.
or keep going straight?

681
00:34:18.927 --> 00:34:20.360
That hill was a little steep.

682
00:34:20.929 --> 00:34:23.932
Might be faster if I take
another route back to the gym.

683
00:34:24.064 --> 00:34:25.299
Yeah. let's do that.

684
00:34:37.879 --> 00:34:40.113
-[jackhammering]
-[sighs]

685
00:34:41.381 --> 00:34:44.318
[♪ suspenseful music plays]

686
00:34:57.832 --> 00:35:00.267
Seventeen minutes
and 34 seconds.

687
00:35:00.400 --> 00:35:01.401
It was her.

688
00:35:01.803 --> 00:35:03.504
I knew I didn't like
that woman.

689
00:35:04.404 --> 00:35:08.042
Ms. Summermann.
there was one file
your office didn't turn over.

690
00:35:08.175 --> 00:35:11.244
I recently hired
a new assistant.
I'll make sure you get that.

691
00:35:11.378 --> 00:35:12.747
I didn't say which file.

692
00:35:14.448 --> 00:35:16.551
But you already know
it was Anna Martello.

693
00:35:16.951 --> 00:35:19.119
Did you withhold information
so we wouldn't find out

694
00:35:19.252 --> 00:35:21.388
that Brody Evans
assaulted Ms. Martello?

695
00:35:21.522 --> 00:35:25.059
And before you protest.
No. we can't prove
there was an assault.

696
00:35:25.192 --> 00:35:28.730
but what we can prove.
from credit card records.
eyewitnesses.

697
00:35:28.863 --> 00:35:31.198
texts and so forth.
is that Mr. Jennings--

698
00:35:31.331 --> 00:35:33.101
-Rest his soul.
-Truly.

699
00:35:33.534 --> 00:35:35.302
He met Ms. Martello
the night he died

700
00:35:35.435 --> 00:35:39.040
then he called
Brody Evans and promised
he'd expose him as a rapist.

701
00:35:39.172 --> 00:35:40.875
Sawyer believed Anna
and so do we.

702
00:35:41.009 --> 00:35:42.409
Good for you.

703
00:35:42.543 --> 00:35:44.211
What does any of this
have to do with my client?

704
00:35:44.344 --> 00:35:47.048
I was never told
about any assault.

705
00:35:47.582 --> 00:35:49.117
Maybe you should look at Anna.

706
00:35:49.249 --> 00:35:50.551
We had that thought too but--

707
00:35:50.685 --> 00:35:53.054
Following Mr. Jennings's
phone call with Brody.

708
00:35:53.688 --> 00:35:59.192
Brody wired
over $100.000 to you

709
00:35:59.326 --> 00:36:01.328
"to make Sawyer go away."

710
00:36:01.461 --> 00:36:03.263
That's a direct quote
from Brody. He's in custody.

711
00:36:03.397 --> 00:36:06.233
And surprisingly.
that man has no interest
in protecting you.

712
00:36:06.366 --> 00:36:08.836
even with all you did
to protect him.

713
00:36:08.970 --> 00:36:10.805
Say nothing else.

714
00:36:10.938 --> 00:36:12.674
By the way.
did you drive here or did
you hop on another scooter?

715
00:36:12.807 --> 00:36:14.909
You know. I can't get through
a whole spin class either.

716
00:36:15.043 --> 00:36:18.445
I get why you ducked out.
except you did it
to kill your partner.

717
00:36:18.579 --> 00:36:20.515
But you didn't know about
the construction you'd hit

718
00:36:20.648 --> 00:36:23.685
on your way back
from shooting him five times.

719
00:36:24.284 --> 00:36:28.723
Or that there was
a camera on that corner.

720
00:36:31.458 --> 00:36:35.262
Liv Summermann. you're
under arrest for the murder
for hire of Sawyer Jennings.

721
00:36:35.395 --> 00:36:37.532
Please stand up.
hands behind your back.

722
00:36:38.633 --> 00:36:40.902
Maybe you'll find
your joy in prison.

723
00:36:41.936 --> 00:36:42.970
Let's go.

724
00:36:45.907 --> 00:36:47.508
[sighs]

725
00:36:54.082 --> 00:36:56.651
[sighs] Oh. good.
You're not going home.
Where's Faith?

726
00:36:56.784 --> 00:36:58.820
She has plans. What do you got?

727
00:36:58.953 --> 00:37:00.922
GBI has been brought in
on a bank heist case.

728
00:37:01.055 --> 00:37:03.858
Polaski and Ormewood
caught a body. Robbers
killed the only witness.

729
00:37:03.991 --> 00:37:06.928
Our theory is
Biosentia Pharmaceuticals
hired the crew

730
00:37:07.061 --> 00:37:09.964
to retrieve stolen documents
hidden at the bank
by an employee.

731
00:37:10.098 --> 00:37:12.499
-Hmm. Tell me about this crew.
-[Angie] We don't know much.

732
00:37:12.633 --> 00:37:14.869
They've hit major hauls
in three separate states.

733
00:37:15.002 --> 00:37:17.672
They are quick.
They are precise.
They never leave a trace.

734
00:37:18.438 --> 00:37:22.342
Oh. so this pharma company
hired the best.
We have any leads?

735
00:37:25.046 --> 00:37:26.748
Oh. We have an arm.

736
00:37:26.881 --> 00:37:28.983
We're trying to ID him.
He's definitely on this crew.

737
00:37:29.117 --> 00:37:31.318
We're narrowing it down
from ten siblings.

738
00:37:31.451 --> 00:37:33.621
Two are deceased. one is a nun.

739
00:37:33.755 --> 00:37:35.590
The point is
we are getting close.

740
00:37:35.723 --> 00:37:39.093
[panting]
Guys. I've got it. Ow.

741
00:37:39.227 --> 00:37:40.427
I got Cheetah Mask.

742
00:37:40.561 --> 00:37:42.830
-The robbers wear animal masks.
-Got it.

743
00:37:42.964 --> 00:37:46.333
Yeah. and Cheetah Mask's true
identity is Preston Willis.

744
00:37:46.466 --> 00:37:47.635
Tattoos match.

745
00:37:47.769 --> 00:37:49.203
Do you have
a last known address?

746
00:37:49.336 --> 00:37:51.706
Yes. I do.
Swanky digs in Buckhead.

747
00:37:51.839 --> 00:37:53.541
Well. I doubt he's gonna flip.

748
00:37:53.674 --> 00:37:55.442
We need to follow him. see
if we can sweep up his crew.

749
00:37:55.576 --> 00:37:57.344
Agreed. We've got one shot.

750
00:37:57.477 --> 00:37:58.880
-Surveillance?
-Ooh.

751
00:37:59.013 --> 00:38:01.115
-Me? Me.
-Okay.

752
00:38:01.249 --> 00:38:02.382
Will. you and Ormewood.

753
00:38:02.517 --> 00:38:05.253
What? [sighs]

754
00:38:05.887 --> 00:38:07.655
-I'm driving.
-Let's go.

755
00:38:07.789 --> 00:38:09.690
-Shotgun.
-Obviously.

756
00:38:11.025 --> 00:38:12.325
[Michael grunts]

757
00:38:13.127 --> 00:38:14.796
[grunting]

758
00:38:17.799 --> 00:38:20.668
Grill's going. He's gotta be
coming back out soon.

759
00:38:21.468 --> 00:38:23.303
[Michael fidgeting]

760
00:38:28.075 --> 00:38:31.679
So. what is this
about you having superpowers?

761
00:38:33.848 --> 00:38:37.218
Well. ever since I finished
chemo. I feel better.

762
00:38:37.785 --> 00:38:40.521
I mean. not throwing up
is always awesome.

763
00:38:40.655 --> 00:38:41.889
I appreciate that.

764
00:38:42.023 --> 00:38:42.924
It just...

765
00:38:43.057 --> 00:38:44.559
seems like
everything's heightened.

766
00:38:45.059 --> 00:38:48.062
I don't know.
I'm probably just imagining it.

767
00:38:50.131 --> 00:38:51.866
I wouldn't dismiss it.

768
00:38:51.999 --> 00:38:54.969
I mean. your whole identity
is "masculine guy."

769
00:38:55.102 --> 00:38:57.071
What? No. I...

770
00:38:58.272 --> 00:38:59.207
Okay. maybe.

771
00:38:59.339 --> 00:39:01.142
No. look. my point is.

772
00:39:01.275 --> 00:39:03.343
that identity
was challenged when
your body stopped cooperating.

773
00:39:03.476 --> 00:39:07.447
Now you're
on the other side of it.
feeling better than before.

774
00:39:07.949 --> 00:39:08.983
I get it.

775
00:39:10.651 --> 00:39:13.020
Thanks. weirdo.

776
00:39:17.024 --> 00:39:19.026
You know. Faith hasn't been
sleeping at home. [sighs]

777
00:39:19.160 --> 00:39:20.995
Tonight will be three days
in a row.

778
00:39:21.128 --> 00:39:23.331
Well. she keeps saying it's
nothing. but it's something.

779
00:39:23.463 --> 00:39:25.933
-Yeah. No.
who's she think she's fooling?
-Not us.

780
00:39:26.067 --> 00:39:27.702
Not us.

781
00:39:28.368 --> 00:39:29.737
[sighs]

782
00:39:30.370 --> 00:39:31.806
But if she's happy...

783
00:39:34.709 --> 00:39:36.409
She seem happy to you?

784
00:39:37.377 --> 00:39:38.613
Very. [chuckles]

785
00:39:40.715 --> 00:39:42.617
Oh. He's coming outside.

786
00:40:01.636 --> 00:40:03.804
Oh. no. [groans]

787
00:40:04.305 --> 00:40:06.207
-You see what I got?
Okay. nice little...
-Look at you.

788
00:40:06.340 --> 00:40:09.310
-Yeah. yeah.
we getting healthy over here.
-Okay.

789
00:40:09.442 --> 00:40:10.678
A little asparagus.

790
00:40:10.811 --> 00:40:11.812
-some shrimp. some protein.
-[phone rings]

791
00:40:11.946 --> 00:40:13.381
-Nice. Nice.
-Yeah.

792
00:40:13.514 --> 00:40:15.316
Oh. Um...

793
00:40:15.448 --> 00:40:16.817
Hi. this is Amanda.

794
00:40:16.951 --> 00:40:18.519
I need you to get
somewhere private right now.

795
00:40:18.653 --> 00:40:19.887
Sorry. this is work.

796
00:40:20.021 --> 00:40:21.421
Oh. no worries.
I'll get the chairs.

797
00:40:21.555 --> 00:40:23.291
-[♪ soul music playing]
-Be right back.

798
00:40:23.423 --> 00:40:25.293
Will. what do you want?
I'm busy.

799
00:40:25.425 --> 00:40:28.863
I need to tell you something.
Ormewood and Angie's
bank heist case...

800
00:40:29.664 --> 00:40:34.001
Malcolm. your Malcolm.
he's part of that crew.

801
00:40:35.435 --> 00:40:38.572
<i>Look. there's no question.</i>
<i>okay? He's dangerous.</i>

802
00:40:38.706 --> 00:40:40.174
[distorted audio]

803
00:40:40.841 --> 00:40:42.643
No. Wait. that's...

804
00:40:44.011 --> 00:40:45.046
You're wrong.

805
00:40:45.880 --> 00:40:48.282
-You're wrong.
-[Will] <i>Look. I'm sorry.</i>

806
00:40:48.416 --> 00:40:49.984
<i>Faith. Faith.</i>

807
00:40:51.018 --> 00:40:52.887
Faith.
he's coming back out now.

808
00:40:53.453 --> 00:40:56.924
<i>Faith. he cannot know that</i>
<i>we're on to him. all right?</i>

809
00:40:57.058 --> 00:40:58.458
<i>-Do you hear me?</i>
-Got it.

810
00:40:58.993 --> 00:41:02.363
-[Will] <i>Faith.</i>
-I understand. Okay.

811
00:41:02.495 --> 00:41:04.098
-Okay?
-Yeah.

812
00:41:04.231 --> 00:41:05.700
All right. Mm.

813
00:41:07.668 --> 00:41:08.903
Okay.

814
00:41:09.870 --> 00:41:12.506
Got the wine glasses. [sighs]

